articles.title: OpenAI denies that it's weighing a 'last-ditch' California exit amid regulatory pressure over its restructuring - TechCrunch
articles.description: OpenAI executives are discussing a potential relocation out of California as increasing political resistance threatens the company's efforts to convert from nonprofit to for-profit status, according to The WSJ, but the company says it has no plans to leave.
